					<head>Pentateuch</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420   lccn.loc.gov/sh85118979" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Pentateuch scroll. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="3r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר תורה</title>
							<note>
								<p>The scroll is made up of a number of fragments pieced together to complete the Pentateuch. </p>
								<p>Exodus, Leviticus, Numbers begin with a new column, four lines being left blank at the end of the preceding column. Every column begins with a new verse, and the initial letter is usually ו. </p>
								<p>The Song of Moses, Exodus 15, and the five lines of text preceding and following it are written according to the rule. </p>
								<p>The Song Ha᾿azinu in Deuteronomy 32 written in 67 lines. It is preceded by six lines with usual initial words, and one blank line. Verses 44-47 are arranged in five lines. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 15th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>76 membranes, 225 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>625</height>
										<width>28680</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>76 membranes, with header (725mm long). </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Dry mould and/or salt accretions.  </p>
									<p>Edge damage and tears. </p>
									<p>Sewing split in a number of places. </p>
									<p>Cracking/delamination at folds. </p>
									<p>Worming and insect damage. </p>
									<p>Bird excreta. Possible rodent urine contamination.  </p>
									<p>Slight water damage. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="225" ruledLines="51" writtenLines="51">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and stiching. </p>
									<p>224 columns in total, one to six columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>Majuscular and minuscular letter in several places. </p>
									<p>Special shape of the letter פ occurs frequently. </p>
									<p>The &quot;puncta extraordinaria&quot; placed on the words fixed by masorah. </p>
									<p>In most of the fragmetns the end of a verse and of a half-verse marked by a dry-point. An upper dry point sometimes distinguishes between כל, את, הוא and כל-, את-, הוא-. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
